1294
01:08:28.476 --> 01:08:31.228
Your little girlfriend.
who do you think?

1295
01:08:31.229 --> 01:08:33.815
Cardozo High School
in Bayside. Queens. right?

1296
01:08:35.316 --> 01:08:36.818
She's in for quite the shock.

1297
01:08:38.277 --> 01:08:40.403
For what it's worth.

1298
01:08:40.404 --> 01:08:42.114
I was hoping
for a different arrangement.

1299
01:08:44.659 --> 01:08:46.035
Something a bit more fun.

1300
01:08:48.788 --> 01:08:50.122
But you blew it. Becket.

1301
01:08:55.169 --> 01:08:56.212
Brian.

1302
01:08:57.338 --> 01:08:59.506
Call Fritzer in Vienna.
We're gonna sell P&G.

1303
01:08:59.507 --> 01:09:00.590
Tell him to name his price.

1304
01:09:00.591 --> 01:09:02.634
Call? Am I allowed to do that?

1305
01:09:02.635 --> 01:09:03.844
What? Just do it.

1306
01:09:03.845 --> 01:09:06.514
Uh-huh.
I've got him right now.

1307
01:09:08.599 --> 01:09:09.683
Yes. ma'am.

1308
01:09:09.684 --> 01:09:12.228
Headed North on Hanover.
That's North. Hanover.

1309
01:09:20.194 --> 01:09:21.195
Sir?

1310
01:09:21.904 --> 01:09:23.029
Excuse me. sir!

1311
01:09:31.956 --> 01:09:34.000
Excuse me?

1312
01:09:40.339 --> 01:09:41.548
He's just not here.

1313
01:09:41.549 --> 01:09:42.675
I don't...

1314
01:09:44.051 --> 01:09:45.136
Is that her?

1315
01:09:45.803 --> 01:09:47.178
Gimme that.

1316
01:09:47.179 --> 01:09:49.014
I'm here. I got your cheques.

1317
01:09:49.015 --> 01:09:52.684
you sociopathic.
conniving bitch.

1318
01:09:52.685 --> 01:09:55.021
Jesus Christ. Becket.
This could've been anyone.

1319
01:09:56.564 --> 01:09:57.898
Call it off.

1320
01:09:57.899 --> 01:09:59.733
Well. just write
the checks first. will you?

1321
01:09:59.734 --> 01:10:01.027
I want to be positive...

1322
01:10:03.237 --> 01:10:04.821
Cheer up. Lyle.

1323
01:10:04.822 --> 01:10:06.156
You're about to make
a lot of money.

1324
01:10:06.157 --> 01:10:08.533
I'm not gonna make
any money. Are you kidding?

1325
01:10:08.534 --> 01:10:12.203
She's just gonna take it
and leave.

1326
01:10:12.204 --> 01:10:14.290
I'm not the one
she wants anyway.

1327
01:10:17.084 --> 01:10:19.962
But you... you're really
coming up in the world. huh?

1328
01:10:22.840 --> 01:10:25.508
Just... Just a little bastard.

1329
01:10:25.509 --> 01:10:27.845
Just a little bastard
from Newark.

1330
01:10:45.237 --> 01:10:47.865
I'd already committed
embezzlement and assault.

1331
01:10:48.950 --> 01:10:50.617
So fuck it.

1332
01:10:51.744 --> 01:10:53.037
Going down.

1333
01:11:40.501 --> 01:11:41.835
Hi!

1334
01:11:41.836 --> 01:11:43.671
How are you?
Thank you for coming.

1335
01:13:25.147 --> 01:13:26.314
On account of the storm.

1336
01:13:26.315 --> 01:13:29.568
I decided to cancel
the festivities tonight.

1337
01:13:31.987 --> 01:13:34.323
But I just couldn't
turn you down.

1338
01:13:37.910 --> 01:13:39.411
Whitelaw.

1339
01:13:41.080 --> 01:13:42.915
Becket.

1340
01:13:45.042 --> 01:13:46.627
Did you bring an appetite?

1341
01:13:50.673 --> 01:13:52.049
So...

1342
01:13:53.384 --> 01:13:56.345
Been working your way
up the financial ladder.

1343
01:13:57.096 --> 01:13:58.472
Is that right?

1344
01:14:01.142 --> 01:14:02.142
Trying to.

1345
01:14:02.143 --> 01:14:04.478
I understand
you've come a long ways.

1346
01:14:05.437 --> 01:14:07.481
Must've really
put in the hours.

1347
01:14:09.316 --> 01:14:12.319
A filthy business. though.
isn't it?

1348
01:14:13.612 --> 01:14:14.822
How do you mean?

1349
01:14:15.823 --> 01:14:16.949
Come on.

1350
01:14:18.367 --> 01:14:20.327
One professional to another.

1351
01:14:22.705 --> 01:14:24.456
you must have. uh...

1352
01:14:25.082 --> 01:14:27.458
broken a few heads.

1353
01:14:27.459 --> 01:14:30.963
bumped off some of
the competition. no?

1354
01:14:33.090 --> 01:14:34.674
Two or three. maybe.

1355
01:14:34.675 --> 01:14:36.510
Would you take any of it back?

1356
01:14:37.678 --> 01:14:39.680
Because
this sort of life is...

1357
01:14:40.931 --> 01:14:43.392
it isn't cut out for everyone.
is it?

1358
01:14:47.688 --> 01:14:50.399
It would make
some people tired.

1359
01:14:51.650 --> 01:14:52.693
Old.

1360
01:14:54.069 --> 01:14:55.112
Lonely.

1361
01:14:56.030 --> 01:14:57.406
Regretful.

1362
01:15:00.618 --> 01:15:05.164
But me. I've always felt
I know a certain truth.

1363
01:15:06.999 --> 01:15:09.125
that the only thing
that really hurts us in life

1364
01:15:09.126 --> 01:15:11.253
is the voice
of our own conscience...

1365
01:15:13.047 --> 01:15:16.550
telling us a story
about right and wrong.

1366
01:15:17.676 --> 01:15:18.885
And if you know
how to turn your head

1367
01:15:18.886 --> 01:15:20.596
just right into the wind.

1368
01:15:21.972 --> 01:15:24.600
you can make that voice
go down to a whisper.

1369
01:15:27.353 --> 01:15:28.771
After a while...

1370
01:15:31.482 --> 01:15:33.359
you might never hear it
at all.

1371
01:15:48.791 --> 01:15:51.085
She was my favorite.
by the way.

1372
01:15:54.004 --> 01:15:56.297
Sharpest of the bunch.

1373
01:15:56.298 --> 01:15:58.341
Always knew what she wanted

1374
01:15:58.342 --> 01:15:59.927
and willing to fight for it.

1375
01:16:02.304 --> 01:16:03.597
Why didn't you help her...

1376
01:16:06.267 --> 01:16:07.518
when she needed it?

1377
01:16:13.065 --> 01:16:15.901
You know where
this is all going. don't you?

1378
01:16:18.737 --> 01:16:20.530
Come on.

1379
01:16:20.531 --> 01:16:22.074
I wanna show you something...

1380
01:16:23.951 --> 01:16:26.620
before Charles
brings out the pudding.

1381
01:16:47.099 --> 01:16:48.350
A trench gun.

1382
01:16:49.268 --> 01:16:51.520
belonged to your
great-great-uncle.

1383
01:16:52.104 --> 01:16:53.522
World War I.

1384
01:16:56.317 --> 01:16:59.277
These... These things
mortified the Germans.

1385
01:16:59.278 --> 01:17:01.029
They'd never seen anything
like it.

1386
01:17:08.912 --> 01:17:09.913
Here.

1387
01:17:10.456 --> 01:17:11.623
Go ahead.

1388
01:17:13.334 --> 01:17:14.335
Go ahead.

1389
01:17:17.463 --> 01:17:19.214
Draw a bead on something.

1390
01:17:26.263 --> 01:17:27.598
I want you to try this.

1391
01:17:31.101 --> 01:17:32.311
Here.

1392
01:17:32.978 --> 01:17:34.188
Right here.

1393
01:18:08.806 --> 01:18:09.890
I better be going.

1394
01:18:10.474 --> 01:18:11.517
Where to?

1395
01:18:14.061 --> 01:18:15.104
Home.

1396
01:18:18.315 --> 01:18:19.691
You're almost there.

1397
01:18:26.240 --> 01:18:27.658
Well...

1398
01:18:30.619 --> 01:18:32.371
you better go quickly then.

1399
01:20:03.295 --> 01:20:05.254
Go on and fuckin' run!

1400
01:20:05.255 --> 01:20:07.924
Doors are boarded up
from the outside.

1401
01:20:07.925 --> 01:20:09.968
- Charles made sure of that.
- Shit!

1402
01:20:17.017 --> 01:20:19.353
There's no way out!

1403
01:20:20.145 --> 01:20:22.523
Go on. Tire yourself!

1404
01:20:23.482 --> 01:20:26.150
Come to my house to kill me?

1405
01:20:27.528 --> 01:20:30.530
You best have done that
when I gave you the chance.

1406
01:20:33.867 --> 01:20:36.203
Okay. Okay.

1407
01:21:43.437 --> 01:21:45.104
Believe this.

1408
01:21:45.105 --> 01:21:48.399
My final murder
was not a murder at all

1409
01:21:48.400 --> 01:21:51.403
but a perfectly legitimate
act of self-defense.

1410
01:21:53.572 --> 01:21:54.947
All right.

1411
01:21:54.948 --> 01:21:56.575
Sheriff's Department's
on the way.

1412
01:21:57.367 --> 01:21:58.451
Okay.

1413
01:21:58.452 --> 01:21:59.702
They're just gonna
talk to you. okay?

1414
01:21:59.703 --> 01:22:02.121
All right. All right. Um...

1415
01:22:02.122 --> 01:22:03.581
I... I need to... I need to go

1416
01:22:03.582 --> 01:22:05.292
'cause I have
my engagement party.

1417
01:22:06.293 --> 01:22:07.376
It started an hour ago.

1418
01:22:07.377 --> 01:22:08.586
Whose engagement party?

1419
01:22:08.587 --> 01:22:09.712
It's mine.

1420
01:22:09.713 --> 01:22:11.547
So you had
no relationship

1421
01:22:11.548 --> 01:22:12.798
with your grandfather?

1422
01:22:12.799 --> 01:22:15.134
I'd never met him
before tonight.

1423
01:22:15.135 --> 01:22:18.179
- Not even once?
- Never.

1424
01:22:18.180 --> 01:22:20.264
Look. if I'm not
legally required to be here.

1425
01:22:20.265 --> 01:22:21.891
I need to leave.

1426
01:22:21.892 --> 01:22:23.309
You're not
legally required to.

1427
01:22:23.310 --> 01:22:25.353
but. uh...
I'd prefer if you stay.

1428
01:22:25.354 --> 01:22:26.313
Okay.

1429
01:23:04.101 --> 01:23:05.434
I'll give you
the full explanation.

1430
01:23:05.435 --> 01:23:07.062
You're withholding
something from me.

1431
01:23:08.355 --> 01:23:10.565
You've been withholding
something from me.

1432
01:23:13.068 --> 01:23:14.361
So right now...

1433
01:23:16.446 --> 01:23:18.073
you have to tell me
what's up...

1434
01:23:19.574 --> 01:23:20.617
or I'm out.

1435
01:23:43.140 --> 01:23:46.726
Sometimes in life.
you gotta take a deep breath.

1436
01:23:46.727 --> 01:23:49.062
come clean
to the person you love.

1437
01:23:52.149 --> 01:23:55.818
This was not
one of those times.

1438
01:23:55.819 --> 01:23:57.486
I only told her
what she'd see on the news.

1439
01:23:57.487 --> 01:23:59.280
... is indeed
dead. and it seems...

1440
01:23:59.281 --> 01:24:00.489
My grandfather was gone.

1441
01:24:00.490 --> 01:24:02.032
...some sort of altercation...

1442
01:24:02.033 --> 01:24:03.827
And as for the fortune.

1443
01:24:04.828 --> 01:24:05.870
well...

1444
01:24:55.378 --> 01:24:56.880
The right kind
of life.

1445
01:24:57.756 --> 01:24:59.424
This had to be it. right?

1446
01:25:01.593 --> 01:25:03.052
Sure. she had
a few misgivings.

1447
01:25:03.053 --> 01:25:05.680
but we can handle that later.

1448
01:25:07.265 --> 01:25:10.392
For now. I was rich.

1449
01:25:10.393 --> 01:25:12.436
And being rich

1450
01:25:12.437 --> 01:25:14.773
is even better
than you imagine.

1451
01:25:25.116 --> 01:25:27.828
You know I mentioned earlier.
this is a tragedy.

1452
01:25:30.163 --> 01:25:31.206
Still is.

1453
01:25:32.457 --> 01:25:34.708
- Donald Macnamara. my wife.
- Hello.

1454
01:25:34.709 --> 01:25:35.918
- Such a pleasure.
- Nice to meet you.

1455
01:25:35.919 --> 01:25:37.753
Nice to meet you.

1456
01:25:37.754 --> 01:25:41.048
- Hi.
- Nancy Dillard. the Dillards.

1457
01:25:41.049 --> 01:25:42.425
- Nice to meet you.
- Mmm-hmm.

1458
01:25:43.218 --> 01:25:44.510
Megan Pinfield.

1459
01:25:44.511 --> 01:25:45.595
FBI.

1460
01:25:48.890 --> 01:25:49.850
Hello.

1461
01:25:53.854 --> 01:25:55.856
Can you shut that door
behind you. please?

1462
01:26:01.778 --> 01:26:05.656
Look. not to be uncouth.
but this is...

1463
01:26:05.657 --> 01:26:06.740
heroically bad timing.

1464
01:26:06.741 --> 01:26:08.200
Yeah. you're under arrest.

1465
01:26:08.201 --> 01:26:09.785
I need you to stay calm
and cooperate.

1466
01:26:09.786 --> 01:26:13.081
- I'm under arrest? For what?
- For murder.

1467
01:26:15.542 --> 01:26:16.668
Of who?

1468
01:26:18.003 --> 01:26:19.337
Lyle Archdale.

1469
01:26:33.226 --> 01:26:34.728
Hey. wait!

1470
01:26:39.900 --> 01:26:41.234
What do we do?

1471
01:26:41.860 --> 01:26:42.903
What do we do?

1472
01:26:45.864 --> 01:26:47.240
Ruth. I love...

1473
01:27:05.216 --> 01:27:06.676
Can you believe it?

1474
01:27:08.094 --> 01:27:09.386
After all this.

1475
01:27:09.387 --> 01:27:11.347
I'd go down for a killing
I didn't even commit.

1476
01:27:11.348 --> 01:27:12.723
Now we wanna
point out to listeners

1477
01:27:12.724 --> 01:27:15.309
that Becket Redfellow
crossed state lines.

1478
01:27:15.310 --> 01:27:18.103
which is why his trial
is unfolding in federal court

1479
01:27:18.104 --> 01:27:20.731
where murder can still mean
capital punishment

1480
01:27:20.732 --> 01:27:23.067
for citizens of New Jersey.

1481
01:27:23.068 --> 01:27:26.570
As we can see
from these security tapes.

1482
01:27:26.571 --> 01:27:28.530
Mr. Redfellow
burst into the office

1483
01:27:28.531 --> 01:27:31.033
at approximately 5:03 p.m..

1484
01:27:31.034 --> 01:27:34.119
and then emerged
just four minutes later.

1485
01:27:34.120 --> 01:27:36.080
which is consistent
with the estimated time

1486
01:27:36.081 --> 01:27:37.707
of Mr. Archdale's death.

1487
01:27:38.708 --> 01:27:41.585
Now. we've heard
from the coroner

1488
01:27:41.586 --> 01:27:43.379
that he estimates
the time of death

1489
01:27:43.380 --> 01:27:45.840
between 5:06 and 5:15 p.m.

1490
01:27:46.383 --> 01:27:47.383
And we've heard

1491
01:27:47.384 --> 01:27:49.134
from the eyewitness
in the hallway.

1492
01:27:49.135 --> 01:27:52.638
who positively identifies
Mr. Redfellow.

1493
01:27:52.639 --> 01:27:55.307
Sir. can you confirm that
this is the murder weapon?

1494
01:27:55.308 --> 01:27:57.643
Uh. I can confirm
that it is. yes.

1495
01:27:57.644 --> 01:27:58.811
And did you find
the defendant's fingerprints

1496
01:27:58.812 --> 01:27:59.937
on the murder weapon?

1497
01:27:59.938 --> 01:28:01.313
I did. yes.

1498
01:28:01.314 --> 01:28:04.108
How certain are you that. uh.
these are his fingerprints?

1499
01:28:04.109 --> 01:28:05.275
I'm 100% certain.

1500
01:28:05.276 --> 01:28:06.361
A letter opener.

1501
01:28:09.572 --> 01:28:12.574
My entire life
because of a letter opener.

1502
01:28:12.575 --> 01:28:15.620
You were the first
to find your husband's body.

1503
01:28:16.121 --> 01:28:17.454
Is that correct?

1504
01:28:17.455 --> 01:28:19.123
Yes.

1505
01:28:19.124 --> 01:28:23.168
Tell me. Were you in love with
Mr. Redfellow at the time?

1506
01:28:25.255 --> 01:28:26.964
Yes.

1507
01:28:26.965 --> 01:28:28.717
And he with you?

1508
01:28:34.723 --> 01:28:37.308
Becket Redfellow
has been in love with me

1509
01:28:37.892 --> 01:28:40.186
his entire life.

1510
01:28:42.230 --> 01:28:45.190
I just never thought he would
do something like this.

1511
01:28:48.403 --> 01:28:49.612
I'm sorry.

1512
01:28:50.780 --> 01:28:52.323
Will the defense
please rise?

1513
01:28:54.534 --> 01:28:55.659
Upon the verdict.

1514
01:28:55.660 --> 01:28:58.495
the jury finds the defendant.
Becket Redfellow.

1515
01:28:58.496 --> 01:29:00.956
guilty of murder
in the first degree

1516
01:29:00.957 --> 01:29:02.291
as charged in the indictment

1517
01:29:02.292 --> 01:29:03.667
and that
the punishment of death

1518
01:29:03.668 --> 01:29:05.002
shall be imposed.

1519
01:29:05.003 --> 01:29:07.129
May the sentence
be recorded by the clerk.

1520
01:29:07.130 --> 01:29:08.964
May God rest his soul.

1521
01:29:08.965 --> 01:29:10.299
Thank you.

1522
01:29:12.969 --> 01:29:14.970
I wish I could find
the right words

1523
01:29:14.971 --> 01:29:17.057
to describe this juncture
in my story.

1524
01:29:22.020 --> 01:29:24.230
Cell 15. secure!

1525
01:29:28.068 --> 01:29:30.195
But there are
no right words.

1526
01:29:33.531 --> 01:29:34.824
There's only time.

1527
01:29:36.868 --> 01:29:38.953
And silence.

1528
01:29:56.930 --> 01:29:58.222
Yo.

1529
01:29:58.223 --> 01:30:00.058
You got a visitor.

1530
01:30:09.818 --> 01:30:11.611
You got three minutes.

1531
01:30:30.922 --> 01:30:33.466
You must be quite the catch
back there.

1532
01:30:39.389 --> 01:30:41.182
You got a big day
coming up. huh?

1533
01:30:43.810 --> 01:30:46.229
You remember that game
we used to play as kids?

1534
01:30:47.438 --> 01:30:49.065
I'd have a secret. and...

1535
01:30:50.108 --> 01:30:51.275
you'd try to guess
what it was.

1536
01:30:51.276 --> 01:30:52.610
If you've got
something to say. say it.

1537
01:30:55.321 --> 01:30:57.115
All right.
I'll give you a hint.

1538
01:30:58.241 --> 01:31:00.618
- It involves handwriting.
- You're foul.

1539
01:31:02.745 --> 01:31:05.373
You're a lump of coal
with makeup.

1540
01:31:07.584 --> 01:31:09.752
I'd rather die in here
than be with you.

1541
01:31:12.672 --> 01:31:14.214
I'll give you another hint.

1542
01:31:16.843 --> 01:31:17.844
Lyle...

1543
01:31:19.429 --> 01:31:21.222
when I found him like that...

1544
01:31:22.849 --> 01:31:24.809
I found something else. too.

1545
01:31:25.727 --> 01:31:27.478
And beautifully written.
I might add.

1546
01:31:27.979 --> 01:31:29.021
What's with the white?

1547
01:31:29.022 --> 01:31:30.814
Are you boys playing doctor
back there?

1548
01:31:30.815 --> 01:31:32.191
Did Lyle leave a note?

1549
01:31:32.192 --> 01:31:34.736
Is that what you're saying?
Did Lyle leave a note?

1550
01:31:36.362 --> 01:31:37.821
- You know...
- If Lyle wrote a note...

1551
01:31:37.822 --> 01:31:39.323
- I think I might just leave...
- If that's what you're saying.

1552
01:31:39.324 --> 01:31:40.490
in the name
of all things holy.

1553
01:31:40.491 --> 01:31:41.701
you have to release it.

1554
01:31:44.495 --> 01:31:46.163
- Oh. now you want to talk?
- What do you want?

1555
01:31:47.790 --> 01:31:50.250
- What do you want?
- Becket...

1556
